author: sussman
msg: Continue issue #685: now that we have ra->get_dir(), teach the
repos_diff editor to display property differences on directories.
* repos_diff.c
(struct_dir_baton):  add pristine_props hash.
(get_dirprops_from_ra):  new helper func.
(open_directory):  call the helper func.
(close_directory):  remove the hack, send both pristine and
'changes' prophash to the callback for comparison.
This is an empty revision for padding.

author: sussman
msg: * reps-strings.c (rep_undeltify_range): fix compiler warning.
* fetch.c (svn_ra_dav__get_dir): duh, use the correct hash index.
(This still doesn't fix the overall problem, which is that ra_dav
still has no way of distinguishing 'svn:ignore' from
'svn:baseline-relative'.  That is, it needs a way of deciding if a
property is stored in the repository, of it only exists in the
network layer.)
